parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ignition key becomes extremely hot
the vehicle will not start on the first attempt
the starter and relay need to be replaced
the ignition sparks and clicks
the vehicle shuts down while driving
the engine surges and cuts off without warning
the power steering and brakes are lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The electrical system shuts down while driving
the vehicle catches on fire
the fuse box catches on fire
the wiring harness catches on fire
the alternator catches on fire
the ignition switch catches on fire
the vehicle is totaled due to extensive damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recall repair can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire despite receiving recall repair
the ignition switch fails after recall repair
the vehicle experiences electrical system failure despite recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not stay in the locked position, leading to a lack of protection for the occupant in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract to its proper position
the seat belt does not stay in the locked position
the seat belt has excessive slack
the seat belt buckle does not release
the seat belt feels tight due to being caught in the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as well as damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
often without warning
and may continue to accelerate until the engine is turned off and restarted. The acceleration can be sudden and unpredictable
making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause sudden acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, as well as damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly.
